&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Safeguarding Team has a vacancy for a Band 7 Named Nurse / Professional for Safeguarding Children 30 hours per week. The successful applicant will be expected to work agilely across the Trust and rotate into the local Multi-Agency Safeguarding Hubs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a forward thinking and innovative team committed to empowering all staff to Safeguard their patients from harm; by providing advice and support, training and supervision. In addition we work with our multi-Agency Partners to ensure that the Trust fulfils all statutory responsibilities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you have extensive knowledge and experience of Safeguarding in your current role, together with a strong desire to make a positive difference to the outcomes of children and their families we will look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust promotes flexible working options on all appropriate positions and our managers welcome these discussions during the recruitment process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMaggie WardJob titleLead for Safeguarding ChildrenEmail addressMaggie.Ward@swft.nhs.ukTelephone number07834802717&lt;/p&gt;
